76561198053132307,Recommended,260730,32618227,Posted: 21 June,all,P.S.,"In all honesty, this is one of the best games ever made. BUT it's unplayable on anything newer than Windows 8, which is incredibly sad. Sure, there is some thingy that will make it run with more than 7 fps, but the developer should do something about it.That being sad, if you have an old PC or Laptop, with that I mean something with an OS that's Win7 or older - install Steam there and play this jewel of a game. This game got it all: some of the most athmospheric western music, absolutely badass characters, great and creative level design, superb voice-acting (I'm playing the German version, so I can't say anything about the English one) and some of the smartest AI I've ever seen: enemies will group up and investigate together, they will get suspicious if one of their friends is suddenly gone and will investigate, and they will even do things like kicking dynamite-sticks you throw at them right back in your face if your not careful.My rating of this game would be:Sound: 9/10 High quality, some gunsounds (Sam's Winchester for example) sound a bit weirdMusic: 10/10 Absolutely amazingGraphics: 10/10 It's an old game, yes, but it looks colourful, alive and detailedStory: 8/10 A western through and through, but with a surprising twist in the end.Characters: 10/10 You WILL love band of misfits you're playing asChallenge and Leveldesign: 10/10 Some missions are easy, and some are REALLY DANG HARD. There is one mission where you're not allowed to get spotted in a certain area of the map, which is a little sucky, but it makes sense story wise and can easily sneak around that area, so it's simply a little extra challenge.Overall: 10/10It's simply amazing, especially for how old it is. For me personally, it is one my very first games ever, and it's still fun and feels fresh today. It's right up there in my top 5 games, together with games like Metal Gear Solid 3 and Civilization IV."
